# navigateForward(_:)

**Instance Method**

Navigates to the next object in the page controller’s arranged objects array, if appropriate.

## Declaration

```swift
@IBAction @MainActor func navigateForward(_ sender: Any?)
```

## Parameters

- **sender**: The sender.

## Discussion

This method is typically invoked in response to a user interacting with a control, the `sender`.

This method is animated and invokes the delegate’s [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPageControllerDelegate/pageControllerWillStartLiveTransition(_:)] and [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPageControllerDelegate/pageControllerDidEndLiveTransition(_:)] methods.

## Related Documentation

- **navigateForward(to:)**: Navigates to the specific object.

## Page Controller Navigation

- **navigateBack(_:)**: Navigates backwards in the page controller’s arranged objects array.
- **takeSelectedIndexFrom(_:)**: Navigates to the selected index, which is taken from the sender.
